@reypolice5231 I still don't follow what you mean by mass. Mass of what? The copper? The ZT value equation does not include mass.

ZT = Seebeck coefficient squared * absolute temperature * electrical conductivity / specific thermal conductivity

The Seebeck coefficient does not include mass. So why would the mass affect it?
